a-driven discoverability.\n• Identify zero‑result searches and implement corrective indexing or transformation logic.\n• Integrate platform telemetry using Google Analytics (GA4) and search instrumentation.\n\nETL, Data Pipelines & Analytics Workflows (Python, Airflow, AWS Glue)\n• Build robust ETL workflows using:\n• Apache Airflow\n• AWS Glue\n• Python\n• Automate search analytics pipelines, metadata ingestion, data quality scoring, and data lake operations.\n• Maintain data pipelines on AWS S3, ensuring schema integrity, partitioning, and performance optimization.\n\nAWS Cloud Engineering\n• Develop and deploy backend services using:\n• Lambda, ECS/EKS, API Gateway\n• SQS/SNS, EventBridge\n• DynamoDB, RDS/Aurora\n• S3, Glue, CloudWatch, X‑Ray\n• Implement cost optimization strategies across compute, ETL, and API workloads.\n• Implement security & governance standards (IAM fine-grained roles, KMS encryption, secrets management).\n\nQuality Engineering\n• Build and maintain robust test suites:\n• Unit testing – JUnit, Mockito\n• Integration testing – Testcontainers\n• Contract testing – OpenAPI validators\n• Load/Performance testing – JMeter/Locust\n\nWork with QA to establish backend te	{}	https://jobs.msd.com/gb/en/job/R389746/Specialist-Search-and-Backend-Engineer	\N	\N	\N	\N	2026-04-09 20:28:16.6
